{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.hubbleConstant_decrease_iff\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">hubbleConstant_decrease_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Meta/Informal/Basic.html#InformalLemma\">InformalLemma</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"There exists a time at which the hubble constant decreases if and only if\nthere exists a time where the deceleration parameter is less then `-1`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.hubbleConstant_decrease_iff","kind":"def","line":179,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.hubbleConstant_decrease_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L179-L183"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.time_evolution_hubbleConstant\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">time_evolution_hubbleConstant</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Meta/Informal/Basic.html#InformalLemma\">InformalLemma</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The time evolution of the hubble parameter is equal to `dÔéť H = - H^2 (1 + q)`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.time_evolution_hubbleConstant","kind":"def","line":174,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.time_evolution_hubbleConstant","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L174-L177"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.decelerationParameter_eq_one_plus_hubbleConstant\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">decelerationParameter_eq_one_plus_hubbleConstant</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Meta/Informal/Basic.html#InformalLemma\">InformalLemma</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The deceleration parameter is equal to `- (1 + (dÔéť H)/H^2)`. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.decelerationParameter_eq_one_plus_hubbleConstant","kind":"def","line":169,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.decelerationParameter_eq_one_plus_hubbleConstant","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L169-L172"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.decelerationParameter\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">decelerationParameter</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a> Ôćĺ <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The deceleration parameter defined in terms of the scale factor\nas `- (dÔéťdÔéť a) a / (dÔéť a)^2`.\n\nThe notation `q` is used for the `decelerationParameter`.\n\nSemiformal implementation note: Implement also scoped notation. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.decelerationParameter","kind":"def","line":159,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.decelerationParameter","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L159-L167"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.hubbleConstant\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">hubbleConstant</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a> Ôćĺ <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The hubble constant defined in terms of the scale factor\nas `(dÔéť a) / a`.\n\nThe notation `H` is used for the `hubbleConstant`.\n\nSemiformal implementation note: Implement also scoped notation. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.hubbleConstant","kind":"def","line":149,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.hubbleConstant","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L149-L157"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.SecondOrderFriedmann\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">SecondOrderFriedmann</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">¤ü </span><span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a> Ôćĺ <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">╬Ť </span><span class=\"fn\">G </span><span class=\"fn\">c </span><span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The second-order Friedmann equation.\nNote: Other sources may call this the Raychaudhuri equation.\nWe choose not to use that terminology to avoid the Raychaudhuri equation\nrelated to describing congruences of geodesics in general relativity.\n- `a : ÔäŁ Ôćĺ ÔäŁ` is the FLRW scale factor as a function of cosmic time `t`.\n- `¤ü : ÔäŁ Ôćĺ ÔäŁ` is the total energy density as a function of cosmic time `t`.\n- `p : ÔäŁ Ôćĺ ÔäŁ` is the pressure. It is related to `¤ü` via `p = w * ¤ü `\n- `w` is the equation of state. We will introduce this later.\n- `╬Ť : ÔäŁ` is the cosmological constant.\n- `G : ÔäŁ` is Newton's constant.\n- `c : ÔäŁ` is the speed of light. It may be set to 1 for convenience.\n\nNote: We will leave `c` explicit for generality and accounting purposes.\n\nAt time `t` the equation reads:\n`(a''(t) / a (t)) = - (4¤ÇG/3) * (¤ü(t) + 3 * p(t) / c^2) + ╬Ť * c^2 / 3`.\n\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.SecondOrderFriedmann","kind":"def","line":127,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.SecondOrderFriedmann","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L127-L147"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.FirstOrderFriedmann\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span>.<span class=\"name\">FriedmannEquation</span>.<span class=\"name\">FirstOrderFriedmann</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a </span><span class=\"fn\">¤ü</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a> Ôćĺ <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">k </span><span class=\"fn\">╬Ť </span><span class=\"fn\">G </span><span class=\"fn\">c </span><span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The first-order Friedmann equation.\n\n- `a : ÔäŁ Ôćĺ ÔäŁ` is the FLRW scale factor as a function of cosmic time `t`.\n- `¤ü : ÔäŁ Ôćĺ ÔäŁ` is the total energy density as a function of cosmic time `t`.\n- `k : ÔäŁ` is the spatial curvature parameter.\n- `╬Ť : ÔäŁ` is the cosmological constant.\n- `G : ÔäŁ` is Newton's constant.\n- `c : ÔäŁ` is the speed of light. It may be set to 1 for convenience.\n\nNote: We will leave `c` explicit for generality and accounting purposes.\n\nAt time `t` the equation reads:\n`(a'(t) / a(t))^2 = (8¤ÇG/3) ¤ü(t) Ôłĺ k c^2 / a(t)^2 + ╬Ť c^2 / 3`.\n\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.FirstOrderFriedmann","kind":"def","line":107,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW.FriedmannEquation.FirstOrderFriedmann","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L107-L125"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\" title=\"declaration uses 'sorry'\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">FLRW</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The structure FLRW is defined to contain the physical parameters of the\n  Friedmann-Lema├«tre-Robertson-Walker metric. That is, it contains\n- The scale factor `a(t)`\n- An element of `SpatialGeometry`.\n\nSemiformal implementation note: It is possible that we should restrict\n`a(t)` to be smooth or at least twice differentiable.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.FLRW","kind":"def","line":92,"name":"Cosmology.FLRW","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L92-L101"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.limit_S_sphere\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">SpatialGeometry</span>.<span class=\"name\">limit_S_sphere</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Trigonometric.html#Real.sin\">Real.sin</a> (<span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/AtTopBot/Defs.html#Filter.atTop\">Filter.atTop</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.limit_S_sphere","kind":"theorem","line":78,"name":"Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.limit_S_sphere","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L78-L88"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.tendsto_sin_rx_over_x\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">SpatialGeometry</span>.<span class=\"name\">tendsto_sin_rx_over_x</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Filter/Defs.html#Filter.Tendsto\">Filter.Tendsto</a> <span class=\"fn\">(fun (<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>) =&gt; <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Trigonometric.html#Real.sin\">Real.sin</a> (<span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhdsWithin\">nhdsWithin</a> <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">0</span><a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Singleton.singleton\">}</a><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#HasCompl.compl\">ßÂť</a>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#nhds\">nhds</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"First, show that limit of `sin(r * x) / x` is r at the limit x goes to zero.\nThen the next theorem will address the rewrite using Filter.Tendsto.comp ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.tendsto_sin_rx_over_x","kind":"theorem","line":71,"name":"Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.tendsto_sin_rx_over_x","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L71-L76"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.mul_sin_as_div\"><span class=\"name\">Cosmology</span>.<span class=\"name\">SpatialGeometry</span>.<span class=\"name\">mul_sin_as_div</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">r </span><span class=\"fn\">k</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ÔäŁ</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">k</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Trigonometric.html#Real.sin\">Real.sin</a> (<span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/Trigonometric.html#Real.sin\">Real.sin</a> (<span class=\"fn\">r</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> (<span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HDiv.hDiv\">/</a> <span class=\"fn\">k</span>)</div></div>","info":{"doc":"The limit of `S (Sphere k) r` as `k Ôćĺ Ôł×` is equal to `S (Flat) r`.\nFirst show that `k * sinh(r / k) = sin(r / k) / (1 / k)` pointwise. ","docLink":"./PhysLean/Cosmology/FLRW/Basic.html#Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.mul_sin_as_div","kind":"theorem","line":66,"name":"Cosmology.SpatialGeometry.mul_sin_as_div","sourceLink":"https://